The best intelligence agencies today do not have a single reliable source in Iran capable of providing information on Tehranâs intentions and capabilities.
While it may not be perfect, the IAEA is the only means of monitoring any nuclear programme in Iran.
Between 1991 and 1998, and despite Saddamâs best efforts from 1992 onwards, the IAEA could not declare Iraq free of weapons of mass destruction.
